<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Clinic Operating System — MVP Development Blueprint</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,300;0,9..144,400;0,9..144,600;0,9..144,700;0,9..144,800;1,9..144,400&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,400&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
*,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
:root{
--ink:#0A0E17;--ink-soft:#131927;--ink-card:#171D2E;--ink-elevated:#1C2438;
--border-dark:#252D42;--border-subtle:#1E2640;
--text-primary:#F1F3F8;--text-secondary:#8A93A8;--text-muted:#5A6478;
--accent:#E8A83E;--accent-glow:rgba(232,168,62,.1);--accent-hover:#F0B94E;
--green:#34D399;--green-bg:rgba(52,211,153,.08);--green-border:rgba(52,211,153,.2);
--blue:#60A5FA;--blue-bg:rgba(96,165,250,.08);--blue-border:rgba(96,165,250,.2);
--red:#F87171;--red-bg:rgba(248,113,113,.08);--red-border:rgba(248,113,113,.2);
--purple:#A78BFA;--purple-bg:rgba(167,139,250,.08);--purple-border:rgba(167,139,250,.2);
--amber:#FBBF24;--amber-bg:rgba(251,191,36,.08);--amber-border:rgba(251,191,36,.2);
--cyan:#22D3EE;--cyan-bg:rgba(34,211,238,.08);--cyan-border:rgba(34,211,238,.2);
--r:14px;--rs:10px;
}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
body{font-family:'IBM Plex Sans',-apple-system,sans-serif;background:var(--ink);color:var(--text-primary);line-height:1.65;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;overflow-x:hidden}
button{-webkit-tap-highlight-color:transparent;touch-action:manipulation;cursor:pointer;font-family:inherit}

/* ═══ NAV ═══ */
.topnav{position:sticky;top:0;z-index:100;padding:0 24px;height:52px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;background:rgba(10,14,23,.95);backdrop-filter:blur(16px);-webkit-backdrop-filter:blur(16px);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-dark);overflow-x:auto}
.nav-btn{font-size:12px;font-weight:500;color:var(--text-muted);padding:6px 12px;border-radius:8px;border:none;background:none;white-space:nowrap;transition:all .2s}
.nav-btn:hover{color:var(--text-secondary);background:rgba(255,255,255,.04)}
.nav-btn.active{color:var(--accent);background:var(--accent-glow)}

/* ═══ HERO ═══ */
.hero{padding:48px 24px 36px;text-align:center;position:relative}
.hero::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:50%;transform:translateX(-50%);width:600px;height:400px;background:radial-gradient(ellipse,rgba(232,168,62,.05) 0%,transparent 70%);pointer-events:none}
.hero-tag{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:10px}
.hero h1{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:clamp(28px,5vw,48px);font-weight:800;line-height:1.1;letter-spacing:-.03em;margin-bottom:12px}
.hero h1 em{color:var(--accent);font-style:normal}
.hero-sub{font-size:14px;color:var(--text-secondary);max-width:520px;margin:0 auto;font-weight:300}

/* ═══ SECTIONS ═══ */
.section{padding:40px 24px;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}
.section-divider{height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--border-dark),transparent)}
.stag{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:6px}
.sh{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:clamp(22px,3.5vw,32px);font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-bottom:6px}
.sp{font-size:13px;color:var(--text-secondary);max-width:560px;margin-bottom:24px;line-height:1.6}

/* ═══ PHASE TABS ═══ */
.phase-tabs{display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:20px}
.phase-tab{font-size:11px;font-weight:600;padding:6px 14px;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--border-dark);background:none;color:var(--text-muted);transition:all .25s}
.phase-tab:hover{color:var(--text-secondary);border-color:var(--text-muted)}
.phase-tab.active{border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--accent);background:var(--accent-glow)}
.phase-content{display:none}
.phase-content.active{display:block;animation:fadeSlide .35s ease}
@keyframes fadeSlide{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(8px)}to{opacity:1;transform:translateY(0)}}

/* ═══ CARDS ═══ */
.card{background:var(--ink-card);border:1px solid var(--border-dark);border-radius:var(--r);padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px;transition:border-color .3s}
.card:hover{border-color:rgba(255,255,255,.08)}
.card-h{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:4px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px}
.card-p{font-size:13px;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.6}
.card-tag{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.05em;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:5px;display:inline-block;margin-top:8px}

/* ═══ FLOW DIAGRAM ═══ */
.flow{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;align-items:center;margin:16px 0}
.flow-node{background:var(--ink-elevated);border:1px solid var(--border-dark);border-radius:var(--rs);padding:10px 14px;font-size:12px;font-weight:500;text-align:center;min-width:100px;position:relative}
.flow-arrow{color:var(--accent);font-size:16px;font-weight:700}
.flow-node.highlight{border-color:var(--accent);background:var(--accent-glow)}
.flow-node.security{border-color:var(--green-border);background:var(--green-bg)}

/* ═══ TWO-COL GRID ═══ */
.grid-2{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(300px,1fr));gap:12px}

/* ═══ CALLOUT ═══ */
.callout{border-left:3px solid var(--accent);background:var(--accent-glow);padding:14px 18px;border-radius:0 var(--rs) var(--rs) 0;margin:16px 0;font-size:13px;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.6}
.callout strong{color:var(--accent)}
.callout.blue{border-color:var(--blue);background:var(--blue-bg)}
.callout.blue strong{color:var(--blue)}
.callout.green{border-color:var(--green);background:var(--green-bg)}
.callout.green strong{color:var(--green)}
.callout.red{border-color:var(--red);background:var(--red-bg)}
.callout.red strong{color:var(--red)}
.callout.purple{border-color:var(--purple);background:var(--purple-bg)}
.callout.purple strong{color:var(--purple)}

/* ═══ TABLE ═══ */
.tbl{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:12px}
.tbl th{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent);text-align:left;padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--border-dark)}
.tbl td{padding:8px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);color:var(--text-secondary);vertical-align:top}
.tbl td:first-child{color:var(--text-primary);font-weight:500}
.tbl tr:hover td{background:rgba(255,255,255,.015)}

/* ═══ SECURITY SECTION ═══ */
.key-visual{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;padding:20px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(52,211,153,.04),rgba(52,211,153,.01));border:1px solid var(--green-border);border-radius:var(--r);margin:16px 0}
.key-icon{font-size:40px;flex-shrink:0}
.key-content h3{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--green);margin-bottom:4px}
.key-content p{font-size:12px;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.55}
.permission-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:10px;margin:16px 0}
.perm-card{padding:14px;border-radius:var(--rs);border:1px solid;font-size:12px}
.perm-card h4{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:4px}
.perm-card p{color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.5}
.perm-card.owner{border-color:var(--green-border);background:var(--green-bg)}
.perm-card.owner h4{color:var(--green)}
.perm-card.manager{border-color:var(--blue-border);background:var(--blue-bg)}
.perm-card.manager h4{color:var(--blue)}
.perm-card.staff{border-color:var(--purple-border);background:var(--purple-bg)}
.perm-card.staff h4{color:var(--purple)}
.perm-card.readonly{border-color:var(--border-dark);background:rgba(255,255,255,.02)}
.perm-card.readonly h4{color:var(--text-secondary)}

/* ═══ ARCHITECTURE DIAGRAM ═══ */
.arch{margin:20px 0}
.arch-layer{padding:16px;margin-bottom:8px;border-radius:var(--r);border:1px solid}
.arch-layer h4{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px}
.arch-layer .items{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px}
.arch-item{font-size:11px;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:6px;font-weight:500}
.arch-layer.presentation{border-color:var(--blue-border);background:var(--blue-bg)}
.arch-layer.presentation h4{color:var(--blue)}
.arch-layer.presentation .arch-item{background:rgba(96,165,250,.12);color:var(--blue)}
.arch-layer.logic{border-color:var(--accent);background:var(--accent-glow)}
.arch-layer.logic h4{color:var(--accent)}
.arch-layer.logic .arch-item{background:rgba(232,168,62,.12);color:var(--accent)}
.arch-layer.data{border-color:var(--green-border);background:var(--green-bg)}
.arch-layer.data h4{color:var(--green)}
.arch-layer.data .arch-item{background:rgba(52,211,153,.12);color:var(--green)}
.arch-layer.security{border-color:var(--red-border);background:var(--red-bg)}
.arch-layer.security h4{color:var(--red)}
.arch-layer.security .arch-item{background:rgba(248,113,113,.12);color:var(--red)}

/* ═══ TIMELINE ═══ */
.timeline{position:relative;padding-left:28px;margin:16px 0}
.timeline::before{content:'';position:absolute;left:9px;top:6px;bottom:6px;width:2px;background:linear-gradient(to bottom,var(--accent),var(--border-dark))}
.tl-item{position:relative;margin-bottom:20px}
.tl-item::before{content:'';position:absolute;left:-23px;top:5px;width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid var(--accent);background:var(--ink)}
.tl-item.done::before{background:var(--accent);box-shadow:0 0 6px rgba(232,168,62,.3)}
.tl-item.active::before{background:var(--accent);animation:pulse 2s infinite}
@keyframes pulse{0%,100%{box-shadow:0 0 0 0 rgba(232,168,62,.3)}50%{box-shadow:0 0 0 5px rgba(232,168,62,0)}}
.tl-phase{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;font-weight:600;color:var(--accent);letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase}
.tl-title{font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;margin:2px 0}
.tl-desc{font-size:12px;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.55}

/* ═══ EXPANDABLE ═══ */
.expand{border:1px solid var(--border-dark);border-radius:var(--rs);margin-bottom:8px;overflow:hidden}
.expand-header{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:12px 16px;cursor:pointer;transition:background .2s}
.expand-header:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,.02)}
.expand-title{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px}
.expand-arrow{font-size:12px;color:var(--text-muted);transition:transform .3s}
.expand.open .expand-arrow{transform:rotate(90deg)}
.expand-body{display:none;padding:0 16px 14px;font-size:12px;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.6}
.expand.open .expand-body{display:block;animation:fadeSlide .3s ease}

/* ═══ FOOTER ═══ */
.footer{padding:32px 24px;border-top:1px solid var(--border-dark);text-align:center;font-size:11px;color:var(--text-muted)}
.footer strong{color:var(--text-secondary)}

@media(max-width:600px){
.grid-2{grid-template-columns:1fr}
.flow{flex-direction:column}
.flow-arrow{transform:rotate(90deg)}
.permission-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav class="topnav" id="topnav"></nav>

<section class="hero">
<div class="hero-tag">Development Blueprint</div>
<h1>Clinic Operating System<br><em>MVP → Production</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">The complete development roadmap from Notion prototype to production platform — including the Owner Key security model, SOP engine, and AI layer.</p>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 1: MVP OVERVIEW -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section" id="s-mvp">
<div class="stag">Phase 1 — The MVP</div>
<div class="sh">Start With What Exists</div>
<div class="sp">The MVP is not a custom-built app. It's a carefully structured Notion workspace + Claude AI layer that proves the concept with real clinics before a single line of production code is written.</div>

<div class="callout"><strong>The Restaurant Analogy:</strong> Before you build a full commercial kitchen, you test the recipes in your home kitchen. The ingredients are the same. The recipes are the same. The only thing that changes when you go commercial is the scale and the equipment. Notion is the home kitchen.</div>

<div class="card">
<div class="card-h">🧠 Why Notion First?</div>
<div class="card-p">Notion gives you 80% of what the MVP needs without writing code: databases, templates, permissions, API access, and a UI your test clinics already know how to use. The 20% it doesn't give you (AI layer, Owner Key, turnover assessment) gets layered on top. You'll outgrow Notion — that's the plan. But you'll outgrow it with real data about what matters and what doesn't.</div>
</div>

<div class="sh" style="font-size:20px;margin-top:24px">MVP Architecture</div>

<div class="arch">
<div class="arch-layer presentation">
<h4>User Interface Layer — Notion Workspace</h4>
<div class="items">
<span class="arch-item">SOP Database</span>
<span class="arch-item">Role Blueprints</span>
<span class="arch-item">Meeting Notes</span>
<span class="arch-item">Decision Log</span>
<span class="arch-item">Vendor Directory</span>
<span class="arch-item">Policy Library</span>
<span class="arch-item">Brainstorm Sessions</span>
<span class="arch-item">Training Sequences</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class="arch-layer logic">
<h4>Intelligence Layer — Claude AI (via API or MCP)</h4>
<div class="items">
<span class="arch-item">Natural Language Q&A</span>
<span class="arch-item">SOP Drafting Assistant</span>
<span class="arch-item">Turnover Gap Analysis</span>
<span class="arch-item">Meeting → SOP Converter</span>
<span class="arch-item">Onboarding Guide Generator</span>
<span class="arch-item">Knowledge Search</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class="arch-layer data">
<h4>Data Layer — Notion API + Knowledge Index</h4>
<div class="items">
<span class="arch-item">Notion Databases</span>
<span class="arch-item">Vector Embeddings (RAG)</span>
<span class="arch-item">Version History</span>
<span class="arch-item">Audit Trail</span>
<span class="arch-item">Role-Tag Index</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class="arch-layer security">
<h4>Security Layer — Owner Key + Access Controls</h4>
<div class="items">
<span class="arch-item">Owner Key Gate</span>
<span class="arch-item">Publish Lock</span>
<span class="arch-item">Role-Based Permissions</span>
<span class="arch-item">Change Request Queue</span>
<span class="arch-item">Audit Log</span>
<span class="arch-item">HIPAA Encryption</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 2: SOP ENGINE -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section" id="s-sop">
<div class="stag">Core Module</div>
<div class="sh">The SOP Engine</div>
<div class="sp">The beating heart of the system. Every process, policy, and procedure lives here — not as a static document, but as a structured, versioned, role-tagged, AI-queryable piece of institutional knowledge.</div>

<div class="sh" style="font-size:18px;margin-top:16px">SOP Lifecycle</div>

<div class="flow">
<div class="flow-node">💡 Brainstorm<br><small style="color:var(--text-muted)">Team session</small></div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node">✍️ Draft<br><small style="color:var(--text-muted)">AI-assisted</small></div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node">👀 Review<br><small style="color:var(--text-muted)">Team feedback</small></div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node highlight">🔑 Publish<br><small style="color:var(--text-muted)">Owner Key req.</small></div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node">📚 Live SOP<br><small style="color:var(--text-muted)">Searchable</small></div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node">🔄 Revision<br><small style="color:var(--text-muted)">Key to modify</small></div>
</div>

<div class="grid-2">
<div class="card">
<div class="card-h">📋 SOP Structure (Notion Database)</div>
<div class="card-p">Each SOP is a Notion database entry with structured fields, not a free-form page. This is what makes it AI-queryable.</div>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>Title</td><td>Text</td><td>Clear, searchable name</td></tr>
<tr><td>Category</td><td>Select</td><td>Clinical, Admin, Billing, HR, Compliance, Equipment, Marketing, IT</td></tr>
<tr><td>Roles</td><td>Multi-select</td><td>Which roles need this SOP</td></tr>
<tr><td>Status</td><td>Select</td><td>Draft → In Review → Published → Archived</td></tr>
<tr><td>Steps</td><td>Rich text</td><td>The actual procedure (numbered, clear)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Owner</td><td>Person</td><td>Who's responsible for keeping it current</td></tr>
<tr><td>Created By</td><td>Person</td><td>Original author (preserved even after they leave)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Version</td><td>Number</td><td>Increments on each published revision</td></tr>
<tr><td>Last Reviewed</td><td>Date</td><td>Triggers stale-check alerts after 90 days</td></tr>
<tr><td>Source</td><td>Select</td><td>Meeting, Brainstorm, Import, Manual, AI-Generated</td></tr>
<tr><td>Publish Lock</td><td>Checkbox</td><td>🔒 Only toggled by Owner Key</td></tr>
</table>
</div>
<div class="card">
<div class="card-h">🤖 AI-Assisted SOP Creation</div>
<div class="card-p">The AI doesn't replace humans — it eliminates the blank page. Here's the workflow:</div>
<div class="callout blue" style="margin-top:10px"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Team has a meeting or brainstorm about a process (e.g., "How do we handle new patient intake?"). Notes are captured in the app.</div>
<div class="callout blue"><strong>Step 2:</strong> The AI reads the meeting notes and drafts a structured SOP — numbered steps, role assignments, decision points, exceptions.</div>
<div class="callout blue"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Team reviews and refines. They add the tribal knowledge ("always check for secondary insurance before calling the patient").</div>
<div class="callout blue"><strong>Step 4:</strong> Manager submits for publication. Owner gets a notification. Owner reviews, uses their key to publish. It's now live and locked.</div>
<div class="callout green"><strong>The magic:</strong> Documentation happens as a byproduct of meetings the team was already having. The AI converts conversation into procedure. Nobody has to sit down and "write documentation" as a separate task.</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="sh" style="font-size:18px;margin-top:16px">MVP Implementation in Notion</div>

<div id="sopExpandables"></div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 3: AI LAYER -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section" id="s-ai">
<div class="stag">Intelligence Layer</div>
<div class="sh">The AI Brain</div>
<div class="sp">An AI that answers from your clinic's own knowledge — not from the internet, not from generic training data. Every answer cites its source. Every answer is grounded in what your team has documented.</div>

<div class="callout purple"><strong>Think of it like this:</strong> ChatGPT is an encyclopedia — it knows a little about everything. This AI is your clinic's longest-tenured employee — it knows everything about how YOUR clinic runs, because it's read every SOP, every policy, every meeting note, and every decision you've ever documented.</div>

<div class="sh" style="font-size:18px;margin-top:20px">How RAG Works (Plain English)</div>

<div class="flow">
<div class="flow-node">🗣️ Staff asks<br>a question</div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node">🔍 System searches<br>knowledge base</div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node">📄 Finds relevant<br>SOPs & notes</div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node highlight">🤖 Claude reads<br>those documents</div>
<div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-node security">✅ Answers with<br>citations</div>
</div>

<div class="callout"><strong>RAG = Retrieval-Augmented Generation.</strong> Instead of the AI making things up, it first retrieves the actual documents from your knowledge base, then generates an answer based only on what it found. If the answer isn't in your knowledge base, it says "I don't have documentation on that" — which itself is valuable information (it tells you there's a knowledge gap).</div>

<div class="grid-2">
<div class="card">
<div class="card-h">💬 Example Queries the AI Can Handle</div>
<div class="card-p" style="line-height:2.2">
<span class="card-tag" style="background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue);border:1px solid var(--blue-border)">Admin</span> "What's our process for verifying insurance on new patients?"<br>
<span class="card-tag" style="background:var(--green-bg);color:var(--green);border:1px solid var(--green-border)">Clinical</span> "How do we handle a patient requesting discharge against medical advice?"<br>
<span class="card-tag" style="background:var(--amber-bg);color:var(--amber);border:1px solid var(--amber-border)">Billing</span> "What's the deadline for submitting claims to Aetna?"<br>
<span class="card-tag" style="background:var(--purple-bg);color:var(--purple);border:1px solid var(--purple-border)">HR</span> "What's our PTO policy for part-time staff?"<br>
<span class="card-tag" style="background:var(--red-bg);color:var(--red);border:1px solid var(--red-border)">Compliance</span> "Who needs to sign the BAA when we add a new software vendor?"<br>
<span class="card-tag" style="background:var(--cyan-bg);color:var(--cyan);border:1px solid var(--cyan-border)">Operations</span> "When did we decide to switch from 45-minute to 60-minute eval slots, and why?"
</div>
</div>
<div class="card">
<div class="card-h">🏗️ MVP AI Implementation</div>
<div class="card-p">For the MVP, the AI layer uses Claude's API with Notion as the knowledge source. Two approaches, both viable:</div>
<table class="tbl">
<tr><th>Approach</th><th>How It Works</th><th>Best For</th></tr>
<tr><td>Claude Project</td><td>Export Notion KB as docs, upload to Claude Project. Staff asks questions in Claude with full context.</td><td>Fastest setup. Works today.</td></tr>
